race.comment: LILLIAN (7) showed plenty of ability last season as a 3-year-old, finishing fourth over 2200m in the LR Belmont Classic at Belmont Park at her last run before having a well-earned spell. She will be a lot stronger now, and looked forward at a recent trial. On top for us. SOUTHLAND (9) was a beaten short-priced favourite and finished fourth last start over 1213m here 3 weeks ago. She is better than that, and with the blinkers on for the first time, she will be among the hardest to beat in this. Follow your money. SPARKLE CORNER (8) stuck on for sixth last start over 1213m here after racing on the pace. That was his first run for his new local trainer, and he needed it. Expect him to finish a lot closer this time. Each way. LEADING TADDY (5) has been out of form for some time, but will find this much easier. A form reversal would not be a surprise. HEZANGELIC (2) needed his fresh-up run here a month ago, and should be some good value at odds in this field. Stick with him.
